{{Infobox artist | name = John Avon | birth_date = {{birth year and age|1961}} | birth_place = [[Cardiff]], [[South Wales]], [[UK]] | nationality = [[Welsh people|Welsh]] | works = [[Magic: The Gathering]] | website = http://www.johnavon.com/ }}
'''John Avon''' (born 1961 in [[Cardiff]], [[Wales]]) is a [[fantasy]] and [[science fiction]] [[illustrator]]. Avon has published a book of his work and his work has been used for book covers, CD covers, games, toys and advertising campaigns.<ref>{{cite web|url = http://www.johnavon.com/|title = John Avon's web site|accessdate = 2011-07-10}}</ref> He is best known for his artworks for the [[collectible card game]], ''[[Magic: The Gathering]]'', of which he has produced over 200 paintings.<ref name="MTGCards">[http://gatherer.wizards.com/Pages/Search/Default.aspx?action=advanced&artist=+%91%22John%20Avon%22&#93 Magic: The Gathering card search for John Avon] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150323054815/http://www.blayney.nsw.gov.au/ArticleDocuments/329/3h%20-%20Hobbys%20Yards%20Heritage%20Items.pdf.aspx |date=2015-03-23 }}</ref>
==Life and work== Avon completed an art foundation course near to where he grew up in Cardiff, and gained a [[BA Degree|BA]] in [[graphic design]] in [[Brighton and Hove|Brighton]].<ref name="wotc-interview">"[http://archive.wizards.com/Magic/magazine/article.aspx?x=mtgcom/feature/117 The quintessential land man: Behind the Canvas: John Avon]", [[Wizards of the Coast]]. Accessed 28 June 2014.</ref> He began his art career in 1983 with commercial advertising.<ref name="wotc-interview" />
He has painted book covers for authors [[Stephen King]], [[Terry Pratchett]], [[Arthur C. Clark]] and [[Harry Harrison (writer)|Harry Harrison]].<ref name=AvonBio>Avon, John. "[http://www.johnavon.com/fantasy-art/biography/ John Avon – Fantasy Art – Biography] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100915030946/http://www.johnavon.com/fantasy-art/biography/ |date=2010-09-15 }}", johnavon.com. Retrieved September 22, 2010.</ref><ref name="wotc-interview" />
Avon is one of the most prolific ''[[Magic: The Gathering]]'' artists, having painted over 280 unique cards,<ref>{{cite web|url = http://archive.wizards.com/Magic/magazine/article.aspx?x=mtg/daily/arcana/1151|title = The Most Prolific Artist|accessdate = 2013-01-21}}</ref> mostly landscapes on 'Basic Land' cards. For the [[World of Warcraft Trading Card Game]], he created the image for the ''Water Elemental'' card which is used in [[Hearthstone: Heroes of Warcraft]].<ref>"[http://hearthstone.gamepedia.com/Water_Elemental Water Elemental]", [[Curse, Inc.]]. Accessed 28 June 2014.</ref>
In 2014 he successfully used the [[Kickstarter]] crowd funding website to raise funds for an illustrated book of his work, ''Journeys to Somewhere Else'' (2015).<ref>"[https://www.kickstarter.com/projects/johnavonart/journeys-to-somewhere-else-by-john-avon 'Journeys to Somewhere Else' by John Avon]", [[Kickstarter]]. Accessed 28 June 2014.</ref>
Avon is married to the illustrator Patricia MacCarthy, with whom he has two sons<ref>{{cite web|url=http://firleartists.co.uk/page19.htm |title=Firle Artists - http://firleartists.co.uk/page19.htm |accessdate=2011-07-10 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120326201630/http://firleartists.co.uk/page19.htm |archivedate=2012-03-26 |df= }}</ref> and lives in [[Saltdean]], near Brighton and Hove, [[England]].<ref name="wotc-interview" /> He also composes, plays and records music on the guitar and piano.<ref name=AvonBio />
==Publications== *''Journeys to Somewhere Else.'' Self-published / John Avon Art, 2015. Hardback {{ISBN|9780993109706}}. Deluxe edition of 500 copies {{ISBN|9780993109713}}. Illustration and text.
