{{more citations needed|date=February 2009}} {{use dmy dates|date=October 2013}} {{Infobox person | name = Ni Min-jan | native_name = {{zh|c=倪敏然|p=Ní Mǐnrán}} | image = <!-- just the name, without the File: or Image: prefix or enclosing [[brackets]] --> | alt = | caption = | birth_name = | birth_date = {{birth date|1946|4|30|df=yes}} | birth_place = | disappeared_date = April 2005 | disappeared_place = [[Taiwan]] | disappeared_status = Found dead (by hanging) | death_date = April 2005 (age 58&ndash;59) | death_place = [[Toucheng, Yilan|Toucheng]] (頭城) in [[Yilan County, Taiwan|Yilan County]], [[Taiwan]] | death_cause = Suicide | body_discovered = | resting_place = | resting_place_coordinates = <!-- {{Coord|LAT|LONG|type:landmark|display=inline}} --> | alma_mater = | occupation = Actor and comedian | spouse = | children = | parents = | relatives = }} {{Chinese name|[[Ni (surname)|Ni]]}}
'''Ni Min-jan''' ({{zh|c=倪敏然|p=Ní Mǐnrán}}; 30 April 1946 – April 2005) was a [[Taiwanese people|Taiwanese]] actor and comedian.
His alleged affair with actress and singer [[Xia Yi]] was suspected of causing his [[suicide]] by hanging, at age 58 or 59, in April 2005.<ref>{{cite web| author = Chang, Rich | url=http://www.taipeitimes.com/News/taiwan/archives/2005/05/02/2003252826|title=Body of Famous Annette Lu Impersonator Found|work = [[Taipei Times]] |date= 2 May 2005|accessdate= 8 October 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last1=Ho|first1=Yi|last2=Woodworth|first2=Max|title=Pop Stop|url=http://www.taipeitimes.com/News/feat/archives/2005/05/06/2003253439|accessdate=25 December 2016|work=Taipei Times|date=6 May 2005}}</ref>
Ni was friends with singer and television personality [[Chang Fei]] and singer [[Frankie Kao]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Dead comedian's identity to be confirmed by DNA|url=http://www.taipeitimes.com/News/taiwan/archives/2005/05/03/2003252941|accessdate=25 December 2016|work=Taipei Times|date=3 May 2005}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last1=Chen|first1=David|title=[POP STOP]|url=http://www.taipeitimes.com/News/feat/archives/2008/09/26/2003424192|accessdate=25 December 2016|work=Taipei Times|date=26 September 2008}}</ref>
