{{Use dmy dates|date=May 2018}} The '''Robert Award for Best Short Fiction/Animation''' ({{lang-da|Robert Prisen for årets korte fiktion/animation}}) is one of the merit awards presented by the [[Danish Film Academy]] at the annual [[Robert Awards]] ceremony. The award has been handed out since 2006.<ref name="SundholmThorsen2012">{{cite book |author1=John Sundholm |author2=Isak Thorsen |author3=Lars Gustaf Andersson |author4=Olof Hedling |author5=Gunnar Iversen |author6=Birgir Thor Møller |title=Historical Dictionary of Scandinavian Cinema |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=QktG6a4YnQYC&pg=PA328 |date=20 September 2012 |publisher=Scarecrow Press |isbn=978-0-8108-7899-0 |pages=328–}}</ref>
