{{for|the architect|Yves Brunier (architect)}}
[[File:Yves Brunier 20061112 Paris Jouets Collections.jpg|thumb|right|Yves Brunier, November 2006.]]
'''Yves Brunier''' (born 1943) is a [[France|French]] [[puppeteer]]. He is best known for his muppet [[Casimir (dinosaur)|Casimir]], an orange colored [[dinosaur]]<ref name="Le musée de la poupée 2015">{{cite web | title=Héros de l'ORTF - la télévision française en jouets des années '60 aux années '80 | website=Le musée de la poupée | date=8 October 2015 | url=http://www.museedelapoupeeparis.com/Heros-de-l-ORTF-la-television.html?lang=en | accessdate=29 March 2017}}</ref> who appears on French Children's TV.<ref name="lefigaro.fr 2015">{{cite web | author=lefigaro.fr | title=L'histoire secrète de Casimir | website=Le Figaro | date=August 26, 2015 | url=http://www.lefigaro.fr/cinema/2015/08/26/03002-20150826ARTFIG00029-l-histoire-secrete-de-casimir.php | language=fr | accessdate=March 29, 2017}}</ref> He played Chelli in ''[[Sacatruc]]'', the French version of ''[[Big Bag]]''. Brunier later went to perform on ''[[Rue Sesame]]'' as Yoyo of 5. He also performed on the ''[[The Muppet Show|Muppet Show]]'' TV pilot.<ref name="Libération.fr 1999">{{cite web | title=Casimir. Depuis qu'il a quitté le costume du monstre gentil, Yves Brunier fait dans l'art moderne. | website=Libération.fr | date=24 August 1999 | url=http://www.liberation.fr/cahier-special/1999/08/24/casimir-depuis-qu-il-a-quitte-le-costume-du-monstre-gentil-yves-brunier-fait-dans-l-art-moderne_280751 | language=fr | accessdate=29 March 2017}}</ref>

